    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "precomputing `computeDeltas()` in forkchoice does improve importBlock, however it increase `notifyNewPayload()` time. Results from `tuyen/prepare_update_head` branch:\r\n\r\n- feature branch:\r\n \r\n<img width=\"1313\" alt=\"Screenshot 2023-05-09 at 08 51 15\" src=\"https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/10568965/236973841-52fc78cb-e73f-46dc-8211-43a4352f0749.png\">\r\n\r\n- unstable branch\r\n<img width=\"1307\" alt=\"Screenshot 2023-05-09 at 08 51 41\" src=\"https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/10568965/236973908-25038f75-104e-4741-8586-523d39e7c2b5.png\">\r\n\r\nit's not worth to put synchronous operations in `importBlock` into `verifyBlock`. In fact, I think most of the time in `notifyNewPayload` is due to the I/O lag issue of lodestar, it's not the real execution engine's time",
